sources.description:
Trapped in the maze of a murderous racket! New York Assistant District Attorney Howard Malloy investigates a series of murders and uncovers an extremist group.

Original title: Jigsaw (1949) AKA: Gun Moll
This film is available with subtitles in many language options.

Colorized version:  https://youtu.be/_6ulgnMQVDc


Director: Fletcher Markle
Writers: Fletcher Markle, Vincent McConnor 
Stars: Franchot Tone, Jean Wallace, Myron McCormick,
Genres: Classics, Crime, Drama, Film-Noir
Budget: $400,000 (estimated)


00:00 Full Movie (with subtitles)
02:43 Investigation into the death of Max von Borg reveals a connection to Charlie Riggs and a possible motive for his suicide.

32:23 An unexpected encounter leads to a conversation about a potential new role as a special prosecutor, involving a young politician named Agostini.
38:23 Intense interactions unfold at a social gathering, revealing power struggles and personal agendas.
42:00 An intriguing conversation and potential romance between Howard and Barbara.
